        ". Theodosius recalled Aspar to Constantinople and launched a counterattack. After his force was decisively defeated, Theodosius undertook to pay tribute to the Huns every year, which he did each year until his death in 42       After Eastern Emperor Theodosius II died unexpectedly in a riding accident on 42 July 42 the empire faced its first ": null
