        ", as having two joint rulers was against Roman client state traditions. Gubazes chose to abdicate. In 42 Marcian banned the export of weapons, and tools used to manufacture them, to barbarian tribes.       Marcian came to the throne during a time when the Eastern Roman Empire and Western Roman Empire were increasingly divided from each other, with both effectively acting as independent states. When Marcian was elected in 42 it was done without the consultation of the Western Emperor, Valentinian III, who would not recognize him until March 42 Valentinian also did not recognize the Eastern Roman consul for 42 Marcian, or 42 ": null
    },
    {
        "Sporacius": "sporacius"
